Installation
===================

System requirements:

tested on:
    os: Linux (Scientific Linux Cern 5 and 6), Mac OS 10.x 
    architecture: x86_64
    compiler: gcc 4.x, clang
   
mandatory:
    Geant versions Geant4.9.6 or greater

    CLHEP (recommended version 2.1.3.1 or greater)

optional: 
    OpenGL (Mesa), ROOT 5.x, 6.x

to compile, see https://twiki.ph.rhul.ac.uk/twiki/bin/view/PP/JAI/BDsimInstall

   %  mkdir build
   %  cd build
   %  cmake ..
   %  make
   %  make install

Getting Started
===================

to run:
    bdsim [options]

f.e. 
    bdsim --file=line.gmad --output=root

to see the full list of options:

    bdsim --help


Some input examples are available in ./examples/ directory. 
For more details consult documentation

Directories
===================

parser/          : gmad parser
examples/        : sample lattices
manual/          : documentation
include/         : header files
src/             : source files
cmake/           : cmake configuration files
test/            : various test libraries
utils/           : various "useful" scripts
vis/             : default visualisation files